Title: Data-driven modeling of nonlinear microwave devices  
Author: B.Schoner and N.Gershenfeld 
Date: (November 29, 1997)  
Address: Cambridge, MA 02139  
Affiliation: Physics and Media Group, MIT Media Lab,  
Abstract: We present an inference-based method for modeling complex non-linear systems that integrates current approaches to modeling of microwave devices within a generalized framework. Familiar techniques for characterizing and emulating linear and non-linear systems are embedded in a fully automated non-linear weighting mechanism, so that globally complex behavior is approximated by a number of simple local models. The framework handles non-Gaussianity, non-stationarity and discontinuity. It offers meaningful parameters, such as Volterra expansion coefficients, and detailed error estimates. 
